h0a34.63,34.63,0,0,1-33.69-26.72,12,12,0,0,0-23.38,5.44A58.64,58.64,0,0,0,1=
50.56,180h.05a58.28,58.28,0,0,0,41.47-17.17l34.75-34.75a58.62,58.62,0,0,0,0=
-82.91Z"></path></svg></button></h3>
<p><strong>1. Data Loading and Preprocessing</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>JSONL files are loaded from <code class=3D"rounded-sm bg-[#e5e5e5] px-[=
0.25rem] py-[0.20rem] text-xs font-normal leading-[15px] before:hidden afte=
r:hidden dark:bg-[#484848]/30">train_data_path</code> and <code class=3D"ro=
unded-sm bg-[#e5e5e5] px-[0.25rem] py-[0.20rem] text-xs font-normal leading=
-[15px] before:hidden after:hidden dark:bg-[#484848]/30">eval_data_path</co=
de></li>
<li>Each sample is tokenized with random truncation if <code class=3D"round=
ed-sm bg-[#e5e5e5] px-[0.25rem] py-[0.20rem] text-xs font-normal leading-[1=
5px] before:hidden after:hidden dark:bg-[#484848]/30">random_sequence_lengt=
h=3DTrue</code></li>
<li>Character intervals are converted to token-level intervals</li>
<li>Samples are batched with <code class=3D"rounded-sm bg-[#e5e5e5] px-[0.2=
5rem] py-[0.20rem] text-xs font-normal leading-[15px] before:hidden after:h=
idden dark:bg-[#484848]/30">per_device_train_batch_size=3D64</code></li>
</ul>
<p><strong>2. Feature Extraction</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Mistral-7B processes tokenized input in <code class=3D"rounded-sm bg-[#=
e5e5e5] px-[0.25rem] py-[0.20rem] text-xs font-normal leading-[15px] before=
:hidden after:hidden dark:bg-[#484848]/30">bfloat16</code> precision</li>
<li>Outputs hidden states for all tokens in the sequence</li>
<li>Feature extractor parameters remain frozen during training</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>3. DETR Processing</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Encoder processes Mistral features with 3 transformer layers</li>
<li>Decoder uses 45 learnable object queries to predict intervals</li>
<li>Each query attempts to predict one AI-generated interval</li>
<li>Denoising training (DN-DETR) adds noise to ground truth for robustness<=
/li>
</ul>
<p><strong>4. Loss Calculation</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Bipartite matching</strong>: Hungarian algorithm matches predic=
tions to ground truth intervals</li>
<li><strong>Focal loss</strong> (<code class=3D"rounded-sm bg-[#e5e5e5] px-=
[0.25rem] py-[0.20rem] text-xs font-normal leading-[15px] before:hidden aft=
er:hidden dark:bg-[#484848]/30">use_focal_loss=3DTrue</code>): Addresses cl=
ass imbalance with coefficient <code class=3D"rounded-sm bg-[#e5e5e5] px-[0=
.25rem] py-[0.20rem] text-xs font-normal leading-[15px] before:hidden after=
:hidden dark:bg-[#484848]/30">label_loss_coef=3D2.0</code></li>
<li><strong>Interval loss</strong>: Combines L1 distance and Generalized Io=
U for boundary accuracy</li>
<li><strong>Auxiliary losses</strong> (<code class=3D"rounded-sm bg-[#e5e5e=
5] px-[0.25rem] py-[0.20rem] text-xs font-normal leading-[15px] before:hidd=
en after:hidden dark:bg-[#484848]/30">aux_loss=3DTrue</code>): Applies loss=
es to intermediate decoder layers</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>5. Optimization</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Gradients computed via backpropagation</li>
<li>AdamW optimizer updates parameters with <code class=3D"rounded-sm bg-[#=
e5e5e5] px-[0.25rem] py-[0.20rem] text-xs font-normal leading-[15px] before=
:hidden after:hidden dark:bg-[#484848]/30">learning_rate=3D0.0002</code> an=
d <code class=3D"rounded-sm bg-[#e5e5e5] px-[0.25rem] py-[0.20rem] text-xs =
font-normal leading-[15px] before:hidden after:hidden dark:bg-[#484848]/30"=
>weight_decay=3D0.0001</code></li>
<li>Cosine learning rate scheduler decays to <code class=3D"rounded-sm bg-[=
#e5e5e5] px-[0.25rem] py-[0.20rem] text-xs font-normal leading-[15px] befor=
e:hidden after:hidden dark:bg-[#484848]/30">min_lr_rate=3D0.5</code> of ini=
tial LR</li>
<li>Warmup for first 100 steps</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>6. Evaluation and Checkpointing</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Validation performed every epoch (<code class=3D"rounded-sm bg-[#e5e5e5=
] px-[0.25rem] py-[0.20rem] text-xs font-normal leading-[15px] before:hidde=
n after:hidden dark:bg-[#484848]/30">eval_strategy=3D"epoch"</code>)</li>
<li>Primary metric: <code class=3D"rounded-sm bg-[#e5e5e5] px-[0.25rem] py-=
[0.20rem] text-xs font-normal leading-[15px] before:hidden after:hidden dar=
k:bg-[#484848]/30">eval_mAP@0.5-0.95</code> (mean Average Precision across =
IoU thresholds)</li>
<li>Best model saved based on mAP score</li>
<li>Only 2 most recent checkpoints retained (<code class=3D"rounded-sm bg-[=
#e5e5e5] px-[0.25rem] py-[0.20rem] text-xs font-normal leading-[15px] befor=
e:hidden after:hidden dark:bg-[#484848]/30">save_total_limit=3D2</code>)</l=
i>
</ul>
