<p>The mean Average Precision (mAP) across IoU thresholds from 0.5 to 0.95 =
serves as the <code class=3D"rounded-sm bg-[#e5e5e5] px-[0.25rem] py-[0.20r=
em] text-xs font-normal leading-[15px] before:hidden after:hidden dark:bg-[=
#484848]/30">metric_for_best_model</code>:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>IoU Calculation</strong>: Intersection over Union of predicted =
vs. ground truth character intervals</li>
<li><strong>Precision-Recall</strong>: Computed at each IoU threshold</li>
<li><strong>Average Precision</strong>: Area under precision-recall curve</=
li>
<li><strong>Mean</strong>: Averaged across all IoU thresholds (0.5, 0.55, 0=
.60, ..., 0.95)</li>
</ul>
<p>This metric balances:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Recall</strong>: Finding all AI-generated intervals</li>
<li><strong>Precision</strong>: Avoiding false positive detections</li>
<li><strong>Boundary accuracy</strong>: Higher IoU thresholds require tight=
er boundaries</li>
</ul>
